channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Off-His-Rocker Carville: 'Racist' Republicans Back Israel Because 'Jews Are Whiter Than Palestinians'
'Cowardly and unacceptable': Progressive NYC Dem condemns violent anti-Israel protest
item.description: Rep. Adriano Espaillat is condemning a violent protest that took place in the quiet upper Manhattan neighborhood of Hamilton Heights this week.

item.title: N.J. Gov. Picks Former Aide to Succeed Sen. Menendez
item.description: Democrat New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy picked his former chief of staff George Helmy to serve the remainder of Bob Menendez's term in the U.S. Senate after Menendez's resignation after being convicted of corruption, the governor's office said on Friday.

item.title: Harris and Walz Bring the Cringe With 'White Guy Tacos' Video, Community Notes Dunks on Them
Walz vs. Vance: New poll reveals which vice presidential nominee is favored among voters
item.description: A Washington Post/ABC News/Ipsos poll found that Democratic vice presidential nominee Gov. Tim Walz has a higher favorability rating than Sen. JD Vance.

item.title: Israeli Official: Blinken, Netanyahu to Meet Monday
item.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu are expected to meet in person on Monday, an Israeli official told Reuters, adding the Israeli delegation at the Doha cease-fire talks would head back to Israel on Friday.

item.title: Has Karma Come for Taylor Lorenz? WaPo 'Looking Into' Post Calling Biden 'War Criminal'
Former NYPD cop-turned-GOP candidate slams 'ludicrous' claims after $120K wrongful arrest settlements surface
item.description: New York Republican congressional candidate Insp. Alison Esposito [Ret.] came under fire on Thursday after details from previous wrongful-arrest affidavits were reported.

item.title: Kyle Rittenhouse to Gov. Walz: Come and Take My Guns
item.description: Kyle Rittenhouse, who was acquitted of fatally shooting two people at a 2020 Black Lives Matter protest in Wisconsin, had a stern message for Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, the Democrat vice presidential nominee, a gun control advocate.

item.title: State funds to Dolton cut as embattled 'supermayor' Tiffany Henyard tries to reinstate indicted police chief
item.description: Some state funds to Dolton, Illinois, have been stopped over the town's alleged failure to submit financial records, where controversial Mayor Tiffany Henyard has been accused of excessive spending.

item.title: Stevenson: The EU Tried to Appease Iran - It Didn't Work
item.description: Abandoned by the West, the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA), has been dead in for years. It was signed by then-U.S. President Barack Obama in 2015 and unilaterally dumped by President Trump in 2018. He described it as the worst deal in U.S. history.

item.title: Of Stolen Valor and the Real Deal
House Oversight investigating Walz over 'longstanding connections' to China
item.description: House Oversight Committee Chairman James Comer, R-Ky., sent a letter to FBI Director Christopher Wray, notifying the bureau of the committee’s investigation into Kamala Harris’ running mate, Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz.

item.title: Andy Harris to Newsmax: 'Bad Idea' for Kamala to Tout Bidenomics
item.description: Rep. Andy Harris, R-Md., told Newsmax on Friday that it's "probably a bad idea" for Vice President Kamala Harris to hit the campaign trail with President Joe Biden, saying it would further tie her to his economic policies.
